               <p>JOSEPH BRAHAM. I lost my hat on the 18th of December, about half past one, it was taken from my chest on the half-deck. The prisoner came on board, the mate of the ship thought he had been one of the men, called him John, he answered, yes; the mate called for some beer, he did not bring the beer, the mate was alarmed; we went and catched him on the half-deck; the hat and handkerchief he had on, they were taken from him at the Thames police; he left his old hat on board the ship.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man belonging to the ship told me to go on board; he would give me a jacket, handkerchief and hat; he owed me some money; his name is 
               <persName id="t18100919-122-person988">
